---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '24 June 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | Sunshine Tiny Houses"
  description="Privacy policy for Sunshine Tiny Houses — how we collect, use and protect your personal information in accordance with the Australian Privacy Act 1988."
  canonical="https://www.sunshinetinyhouses.com.au/privacy-policy/"
  noindex={true}
>

  <section class="page-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="page-hero__sub">Last updated {updated}</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container policy-wrap">

      <p>Sunshine Tiny Houses (ABN 40 270 427 080) ("we", "us", "our") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, disclose and store your personal information in accordance with the <em>Privacy Act 1988</em> (Cth) and the Australian Privacy Principles (APPs).</p>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect personal information you provide directly to us, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Your name, phone number and email address (via our contact and quote forms)</li>
        <li>Your property address or suburb (to assess delivery and site requirements)</li>
        <li>Details about your building project (shared during consultations or via our forms)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We also collect non-personal information automatically when you visit our website, including your IP address, browser type, pages visited and time spent on pages — collected via cookies and analytics tools (see section 4).</p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Your Information</h2>
      <p>We use your personal information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Respond to your enquiries and provide quotes</li>
        <li>Communicate with you throughout the design and build process</li>
        <li>Send you relevant updates about your project</li>
        <li>Improve our website and marketing based on aggregate usage data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will not use your information for any purpose you would not reasonably expect.</p>

      <h2>3. Disclosure of Your Information</h2>
      <p>We do not sell or trade your personal information. We may share it with:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Finance partners</strong> (Emu Money, Handypay) — only if you request a finance referral</li>
        <li><strong>Delivery contractors</strong> — only the information needed to coordinate transport of your build</li>
        <li><strong>Service providers</strong> — such as our form processing service (FormSubmit) who handle enquiry emails on our behalf, under confidentiality obligations</li>
        <li><strong>Authorities</strong> — if required by law or to protect our legal rights</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>4. Cookies and Analytics</h2>
      <p>Our website uses the following third-party tools that may set cookies on your device:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics 4</strong> — collects anonymised data about how visitors use our site (pages viewed, time on site, referral source). Data is processed by Google LLC in accordance with their privacy policy. You can opt out via <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's opt-out tool</a>.</li>
        <li><strong>Meta Pixel</strong> — used on our advertising landing pages to measure the effectiveness of our Facebook and Instagram ads. Data is processed by Meta Platforms Inc. You can manage your ad preferences via <a href="https://www.facebook.com/ads/preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Facebook's Ad Preferences</a>.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can disable cookies in your browser settings, though this may affect the functionality of some pages.</p>

      <h2>5. Data Storage and Security</h2>
      <p>Your personal information is stored securely. Enquiry data submitted via our contact forms is transmitted to our email inbox via FormSubmit (a third-party form processing service) and stored in our email system.</p>
      <p>We take reasonable steps to protect your information from misuse, loss, unauthorised access, modification or disclosure. However, no internet transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of data sent to us online.</p>

      <h2>6. How Long We Keep Your Information</h2>
      <p>We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfil the purpose for which it was collected and to comply with any legal obligations. Enquiry and project records are generally kept for 7 years in accordance with standard business record-keeping requirements.</p>

      <h2>7. Access and Correction</h2>
      <p>You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you, and to ask us to correct any inaccuracies. To make a request, contact us at the details below. We will respond within 30 days.</p>

      <h2>8. Complaints</h2>
      <p>If you believe we have handled your personal information in a way that does not comply with the Australian Privacy Principles, you may make a complaint by contacting us. We will investigate and respond within 30 days.</p>
      <p>If you are not satisfied with our response, you may contact the <a href="https://www.oaic.gov.au" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Office of the Australian Information Commissioner (OAIC)</a>.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time. The current version will always be available at this URL with the date of the last update shown at the top.</p>

      <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>For any privacy-related enquiries or requests:</p>
      <address>
        <strong>Sunshine Tiny Houses</strong><br />
        24 Venture Drive, Noosaville QLD 4566<br />
        <a href="mailto:hello@sunshinetinyhouses.com.au">hello@sunshinetinyhouses.com.au</a><br />
        <a href="tel:0753158365">(07) 5315 8365</a>
      </address>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
.page-hero {
  background: var(--color-surface-dark);
  color: #fff;
  padding: 4rem 0 3rem;
}
.page-hero h1 { color: #fff; }
.page-hero__sub { color: rgba(255,255,255,.6); margin-top: .5rem; font-size: .95rem; }

.policy-wrap {
  max-width: 760px;
}
.policy-wrap > p,
.policy-wrap > ul,
.policy-wrap > address {
  color: var(--color-text-body);
  line-height: 1.75;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}
.policy-wrap h2 {
  font-size: 1.15rem;
  margin-top: 2.5rem;
  margin-bottom: .75rem;
  padding-top: 1.5rem;
  border-top: 1px solid var(--color-border);
}
.policy-wrap h2:first-of-type { margin-top: 2rem; }
.policy-wrap ul {
  padding-left: 1.35rem;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: .4rem;
}
.policy-wrap ul li { font-size: .95rem; }
.policy-wrap a {
  color: var(--color-primary);
  text-decoration: underline;
  text-underline-offset: 2px;
}
.policy-wrap address {
  font-style: normal;
  background: var(--color-surface);
  border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  margin-top: .5rem;
}
</style>
